title: Ex-ministers Manusha, Ramesh Pathirana lose their seats
byline: Former Ministers Ramesh Pathirana and Manusha Nanayakkara have lost their seats in the Galle district in 2024 general election.

title: NPP wins four seats in Polonnaruwa, Daham Sirisena out
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured four seats in the Polonnaruwa District, garnering 68.67% of the total votes. Meanwhile, the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) won one seat in the district.

title: NPP exceeds 2 million total votes
byline: The National People’s Power has secured a total of 2,075,976 votes at the Parliamentary Elections 2024 so far.

title: NPP wins five seats in Hambantota District
byline: The National People’s Power secured five seats in the Hambantota District, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya and the Sri Lanka Podujana Party secured a seat each.

title: NPP wins seven seats from Galle District
byline: The National People’s Power won seven seats from the Galle District, after polling 68.07% of the total valid votes cast, while Samagi Jana Balawegeya and Sri Lanka Podujana Party received one seat each.

title: ITAK wins Batticaloa District postal votes
byline: Ilankai Tamil Arasu Kadchi (ITAK)won the postal vote in Batticaloa District securing 5,236 votes.

title: NPP lead by over 1 million votes over SJB
byline: The total votes for the National People’s Power at the Parliamentary Elections 2024, stood at 1,391,347, following the latest results from the Mahiyangana polling division of the Badulla district.

title: NPP wins Nallur polling division in Jaffna District
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP)won the Jaffna Poling Division with 8,831 votes.

title: NPP secures resounding victory in Colombo district postal voting
byline: The National People’s Power secured another resounding victory, with 80% of the Postal votes in the Colombo district.

title: NPP wins Galle Polling Division with 39,707 votes
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) won the Galle Polling Division securing 39,707 votes.

title: T. B. Sarath tops preferential votes in Polonnaruwa
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured four seats in the Polonnaruwa District, with T. B. Sarath receiving the highest number of preferential votes in the district.

title: ITAK secures three seats in Batticaloa district
byline: The Illankai Tamil Arasu Kachchi (ITAK) has secured three seats in the Batticaloa district with 96,975 votes, while the National People’s Power (NPP) won one seat with 55,498 votes.

title: NPP wins 9 seats in Kandy, SJB 2 seats
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured nine seats in the Kandy District with 500,596 votes. The Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) secured two seats with 145,939 votes, while the New Democratic Front (NDF) secured one seat with 50,889 votes.

title: NPP wins 6 seats; SJB 2 in Puttalam district
byline: The National People’s Power secured six seats in the Puttalam District, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya secured two seats.

title: NPP dominates Jaffna district, wins 3 seats
byline: Signifying one of their biggest turnarounds at this year’s Parliamentary Elections, the National People’s Power won the most seats from the Jaffna District, taking three of the six available electoral seats.

title: NPP secures 8 seats in Ratnapura District, Pavithra out
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured 8 seats in the Ratnapura District with 368,229 votes, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) secured three seats with 133,041

title: NPP wins 12 seats in Kurunegala; Johnston out
byline: The National People’s Power secured 12 seats in the Kurunegala District, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya secured three seats.

title: NPP wins 7 seats, SJB 2 in Kegalle District
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured seven seats in the Kegalle District with 312,441 votes, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) won two seats with 109,691 votes.

title: NPP wins 7 seats, SJB 2 in Anuradhapura district
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured seven seats in the Anuradhapura District while securing 331, 692 votes.

title: NPP secures two seats in Vanni District
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured two seats in the Vanni District with 39,894 votes. The Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB), Ilankai Tamil Arasu Kachchi (ITAK), Democratic Tamil National Alliance (DTNA), and Sri Lanka Labour Party (SLLP) secured one seat each.

title: NPP wins 8 seats, SJB 2 in Kalutara district
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured eight seats in the Kalutara District while securing 452, 398 votes.

title: Five seats for NPP in Nuwara Eliya
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured five seats in the Nuwara Eliya district, having accounted for more than 40% of the total valid votes.

title: NPP surpasses 5 million total votes; 39 seats so far
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) has surpassed five million votes so far securing a total of 5,000,296 votes in the general election.

title: NPP wins 4 seats, SJB 1 in Matale District
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured four seats in the Matale District, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) won one seat.

title: Two seats for NPP from Trincomalee
byline: In one of the more closely contested districts, the National People’s Power (NPP) secured a majority of the electoral seats for the Trincomalee District, winning two out of four seats.

title: NPP wins 6 seats in Badulla, SJB secures 2, NDF 1
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured six seats in the Badulla District, capturing 58.59% of the total votes. The Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) won two seats, while the New Democratic Front (NDF) secured one seat.

title: NPP secures five seats in Monaragala
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) has secured five seats in the Monaragala district, while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) has won one seat.

title: NPP secures 22 seats, SJB 4, SLPP 2 in four districts
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) has secured 22 seats from the final results issued for four districts so far.

title: Kanchana Wijesekera out
byline: Former Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera has lost his parliamentary seat in the Matara district, as the New Democratic Front (NDF) failed to secure any seats in the 2024 General Election.

title: Vijitha tops highest in preferential vote history
byline: NPP Gampaha District team leader Vijitha Herath becomes the highest ever preferential vote taker in history by receiving 716, 715 votes, even surpassing NPP Colombo District team leader Dr. Harini Amarasuriya, who set a record by obtaining 655, 289 a short while ago.

title: Will not misuse excessive power given by the people: NPP
byline: Claiming that it is a huge challenge to keep the trust placed by the people on the National People’s Power (NPP), NPP member Tilvin Silva said today the NPP government will make sure that the excessive power given to the NPP will not be misused and is committed to use for the benefit of the people and to uphold democratic rights of the people.

title: Namal Karunaratne tops Kurunegala: Nalin, Dayasiri secure seats for SJB
byline: Namal Karunaratne of the National People’s Power (NPP) secured the highest number of preferential votes in the Kurunegala District, with a total of 356,969 votes. NPP’s Ananda Wijeyapala and Sujeeva Dissanayake followed in second and third places respectively.

title: Lal Kantha tops Kandy, Kiriella’s daughter enters Parliament
byline: The preferential vote results for the Kandy District in the 2024 General Election have been released and NPP’s K.D. Lal Kantha secured the highest number of preferential votes in Kandy, with 316,951 votes.

title: Nalinda Jayatissa tops Kalutara; Rajitha and Vidura out
byline: Nalinda Jayatissa secured the highest preferential votes in the Kalutara District, amassing 371,640 votes.

title: Sajith, Harsha, Mujibur and Marikkar enter Parliament from SJB Colombo list
byline: Samagi Jana Balawegaya leader Sajith Premadasa along with members Dr. Harsha de Silva, Mujibur Rahuman and S. M. Marikkar have been elected to the Parliament with highest preferential votes.

title: Harini records highest preferential votes, surpassing MR’s 2020 tally
byline: Harini Amarasuriya of the National People’s Power (NPP) set a new record by securing the highest preferential votes in Colombo in the 2024 General Elections, with 655,289 votes.

title: Rohitha in, Mahindananda out
byline: New Democratic Front (NDF) Kalutara District candidate Rohitha Abeygunawardena also known as ‘Raththaran’ had managed to secure his seat through the 2024 General Elections, whereas Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna (SLPP) stalwart from Kandy District Mahindananda Aluthgamage has lost his position.

title: Japanese Ambassador congratulates newly elected Parliament
byline: Japanese Ambassador to Sri Lanka H.E. Akio Isomata congratulating the newly elected Parliament commended the people of Sri Lanka for their active engagement for a peaceful and democratic parliamentary election.

title: Sarath Weerasekera, Sagala Ratnayake defeated in Colombo District
byline: Former Minister of Public Security Sarath Weerasekera failed to secure a seat in the Parliamentary Elections 2024 in the Colombo District, along with New Democratic Front candidate Sagala Ratnayake.

title: President thanks all who voted for renaissance
byline: President Anura Kumara Dissanayake thanked all who voted for a renaissance.

title: Harin, Ruwan and Rehan defeated in bid for Parliament seat
byline: Harin Fernando and Ruwan Wijewardene, who both contested under the New Democratic Front (NDF) in the Badulla and Gampaha District respectively have been defeated.

title: Sumanthiran voted out in Jaffna
byline: Leading member of Ilankai Tamil Arachcu Katchchi (ITAK) M.A. Sumanthiran has not been elected to Parliament from the Jaffna district. The sole seat for the ITAK in the district has been won by Mr. S.Sritharan.

title: UDV is still young, we didn’t have time to campaign: Ranjan
byline: Defeated candidate from the Gampaha district Ranjan Ramanayake said he and his party, the United Democratic Voice (UDV) did not have enough time to campaign ahead of the Parliamentary Elections.

title: Sunil Handunneththi tops preferential votes in Matara
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured six seats in the Matara District, with Sunil Handunneththi receiving the highest number of preferential votes in the district.

title: NPP wins four seats in Digamadulla
byline: The National People’s Power secured four seats in the Digamadulla District, having received 146,313 votes.

title: Namal congratulates Anura, NPP
byline: Former Minister Namal Rajapaksa extended his congratulations to President Aruna Kumara Dissanayake and the National People’s Power (NPP) on their sweeping win in the Parliamentary Elections this morning.

title: NPP wins 14 seats in Colombo
byline: The National People’s Power (NPP) secured 14 seats in the Colombo District with 788,636 votes. The Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) secured four seats with 208,249 votes.
